      "title": "Current Profitability and Margin Recovery Analysis",
      "description": "Analyse the financial health of a small Bristol bakery with annual revenue of £180,000, 3 full-time staff, and net profit margin decline from 14% two years ago to 8% now. The main reported cost pressure is a 22% rise in ingredient costs. Determine what actions could restore margins before considering major expansion. Consider pricing, product mix, ingredient sourcing, waste reduction, labour productivity, menu engineering, and whether the business can realistically return toward prior profitability levels.",
      "expertise_needed": "Small business finance specialist or hospitality accountant with bakery/food-service experience",
      "expected_output": "A concise financial diagnosis with estimated profit impact of key levers, recommended margin-restoration actions, risks, and priority order for implementation."
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "title": "Competitive Positioning and Revenue Recovery Strategy",
      "description": "Develop a revenue and positioning strategy for an independent Bristol bakery facing a new Greggs located 200 metres away, which has reduced its lunchtime sandwich trade. The bakery retains approximately 400 loyal regular customers and has strong reputation signals: sourdough and pastries rated 4.8 stars on Google from 180 reviews. Assess how the bakery should respond commercially without trying to compete directly with Greggs on price. Consider customer segmentation, product differentiation, premium positioning, loyalty programmes, corporate/local partnerships, breakfast and weekend trade, subscriptions, and ways to replace lost lunchtime sandwich revenue.",
      "expertise_needed": "Food retail marketing strategist or independent café/bakery growth consultant",
      "expected_output": "A practical revenue recovery plan with target customer segments, recommended offers or campaigns, positioning guidance, and measurable actions for the next 3–6 months."
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "title": "Delivery Partnership Evaluation",
      "description": "Evaluate whether the bakery should accept a delivery partnership offered by a local food influencer with 28,000 followers. The influencer would sell through her platform and charge an 18% commission. The bakery has strong products, especially sourdough and pastries, and a loyal local customer base, but current net margin is only 8%. Assess whether delivery through this channel is financially and operationally attractive, including commission impact, packaging and delivery suitability, cannibalisation risk, customer acquisition value, brand fit, and recommended trial structure.",
      "expertise_needed": "E-commerce food delivery strategist or hospitality unit economics analyst",
      "expected_output": "A go/no-go recommendation or trial design, including unit economics considerations, suitable product types, minimum margin requirements, performance metrics, and contract terms to negotiate."
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "title": "Second Location Feasibility Assessment",
      "description": "Assess the feasibility of opening a second bakery location in Clifton, Bristol, where there is reportedly no artisan bakery. The existing bakery has annual revenue of £180,000, 3 full-time staff, £35,000 in savings, and possible access to a £50,000 SEIS-backed loan from a family friend. Current net profit margins have fallen to 8%, and the owner’s partner favours expansion while the accountant recommends fixing margins first. Evaluate whether a second site is strategically and financially prudent at this stage, including likely startup costs, staffing needs, management capacity, break-even revenue, funding risk, and criteria that should be met before expansion.",
      "expertise_needed": "Hospitality expansion consultant or small business investment analyst",
      "expected_output": "A feasibility assessment with key assumptions, major risks, capital requirements, break-even considerations, and a recommendation on whether to proceed now, delay, or test the market first."
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "title": "Lease Renewal and Capital Risk Strategy",
      "description": "Develop a risk management strategy for the bakery’s current premises given that the lease is up for renewal in 14 months and the landlord has indicated a 15% rent increase. The bakery currently generates £180,000 annual revenue with net profit margin of 8%, has £35,000 savings, and may access a £50,000 SEIS-backed loan from a family friend. Assess how the lease renewal should influence near-term decisions, including negotiation strategy, affordability of higher rent, relocation contingency planning, use of savings or debt, and whether committing capital to expansion before lease certainty is advisable.",
      "expertise_needed": "Commercial property advisor or SME financial risk consultant",
      "expected_output": "A lease and capital risk plan covering negotiation priorities, financial thresholds, contingency options, recommended timing, and implications for borrowing or expansion decisions."
    }
  ]
}

